<br>
Airgiod held tight to the tiny girl, a copy of her sister, now gone from her.  She whispered in the old tongue, studying the child closely.  <br>
<br>
She had a thick mat of white hair and clear lavender eyes.  Eyes that looked curiously around from beneath the wrappings the druidess had gathered up.<br>
<br>
She looked as if she was taking notes, Airgiod thought. As if she knew her time with her mother was limited.<br>
<br>
The druidess paced, looking worried.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
Airgiod, I have to get that child to Davin, before he makes the other one known.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Airgiod looked up at the druidess, having nearly forgotten her presence.<br>
<br>
She nodded mutely, and showered kisses over the baby.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
I love you. Always, I love you, and your sister. May the two of you draw strength from each other, always.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Airgiod sighed, and gave up her daughter.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><center><b>Airgiod</b><br>
